Captive Pursuit: Through a new friendship with a bizarre alien, O'Brien and the rest of the officers of Deep Space Nine learn that other beings do not respect life as much as they do.
Learning Curve: O'Neill risks a potential court-martial in order to teach a young alien girl the joys of childhood. (S3, ep 5)
Live Fast and Prosper: A pair of con artists attempt to trade with a mining colony by impersonating Tuvok and Captain Janeway. (S6, Ep 21)
Sub Rosa: Shortly after her grandmother's death, Beverly falls under the spell of a ghost lover who has been in her family for generations. (S7, ep 14)
Jurassic Mall: Cutter grapples with Claudia's disappearance after he returns to a different present. The team are called in to capture raptors on the loose at a shopping centre. (S2, ep 1)
Sisterhood: A drug dealer is shot in a federal park and the team sets out to look for his killer. Maggie's sister returns to New York. (S5, ep 19)
Privilege: All eyes are on the team when they try to find out who kidnapped the child of a senator, but the abduction reveals a link to a similar case. (S5, ep 20)
The Taming Of The Wu: Wu's bite begins to have serious unforeseen consequences, as Adalind finds herself backed into a corner and forced to make a choice. (S5, ep 19)
Old Souls: Not for the first time, events in Purgatory are set for an apocalyptic conclusion. (S4, ep 12)
Sharing shifts with Cambridgeshire's police force, this documentary reveals what life on the beat is really like. Contains strong language and some distressing scenes. (4/10)

Q-Less: Frequent Enterprise visitors Q and Vash introduce themselves to the crew of Deep Space Nine, while the officers struggle to save the station from imminent destruction.
Point Of View: When an alternate reality of Earth is invaded by the Goa'uld, their version of Dr Samantha Carter, along with Major Kawalsky, seeks refuge with Stargate Command. (S3, ep 6)
Muse: Kim goes missing in an escape pod, and Torres becomes stranded on a pre-warp planet where a playwright is recreating the Voyager's story. (S6, Ep 22)
Lower Decks: While enduring the process which assesses crew-members seeking promotion on the Enterprise, four junior officers find themselves involved in a top-secret mission.
Mealworms, Indeed: An anomaly appears inside an office tower, filling it with fog and gigantic worms. New team member Jenny Lewis comes to terms with the dangers of her new job. (S2, ep 2)
Bad Guy: Vince's judgement is compromised when a harrowing rescue involving two children triggers emotional trauma from when his daughter passed away. (S1, ep 8)
Uprooting: When an American vintner is shot and killed on his wine estate in France, the Fly Team must determine if the local protest group is to blame. (S1, ep 17)
Bad Night: Nick worries his losses may grow in the battle against Black Claw and sets his sights on Renard, whose eyes are on the approaching election. (S5, ep 20)
